<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-12-17T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-12-17T19:00:00-05:00" n="228" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d228">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15/834: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-12-17T19:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">December 17,
                                        1928—7 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>109. Your 123, December 17, noon. You can tell Drummond that this
                            Government is prepared to send delegates at any time. The dates
                            mentioned are satisfactory but we should also be satisfied with an
                            earlier date.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>